  11,9,"If We give people a taste of Our mercy then take it away from them, they become utterly desperate, ungrateful"
  11,10,"But if We give them a taste of prosperity after being touched with adversity, they say, ‚ÄúMy ills are gone,‚ÄĚ and become totally prideful and boastful"
  11,11,except those who patiently endure and do good. It is they who will have forgiveness and a mighty reward
  11,12,"Perhaps you ňĻO Prophetňļ may wish to give up some of what is revealed to you and may be distressed by it because they say, ‚ÄúIf only a treasure had been sent down to him, or an angel had come with him!‚ÄĚ You are only a warner, and God is the Trustee of All Affairs"
  11,13,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe¬†has fabricated this ňĻQuranňļ!‚ÄĚ? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúProduce ten fabricated s√Ľrahs like it and seek help from whoever you can‚ÄĒother than God‚ÄĒif what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  11,14,"But if your helpers fail you, then know that it has been revealed with the knowledge of God, and that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him! Will you ňĻnotňļ then submit ňĻto Godňļ"
  11,15,"Whoever desires ňĻonlyňļ this worldly life and its luxuries, We will pay them in full for their deeds in this life‚ÄĒnothing will be left out"
  11,16,It is they who will have nothing in the Hereafter except the Fire. Their efforts in this life will be fruitless and their deeds will be useless
  11,17,"ňĻCan these people be compared toňļ those ňĻbelieversňļ who stand on clear proof from their Lord, backed by ňĻthe Quran asňļ a witness from Him, and preceded by the Book of Moses ňĻwhich was revealedňļ as a guide and mercy? It is those ňĻbelieversňļ who have faith in it. But whoever from the ňĻdisbelievingňļ groups¬†rejects it, the Fire will be their destiny. So do not be in doubt of it. It is certainly the truth from your Lord, but most people do not believe"
  11,18,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against God? They will be brought before their Lord, and the witnesses¬†will say, ‚ÄúThese are the ones who lied against their Lord.‚ÄĚ Surely God‚Äôs condemnation is upon the wrongdoers"
